  "prompt": "Does money laundering fall under criminal legislation?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a criminal offense in most jurisdictions around the world. It is typically addressed under criminal legislation and financial crime statutes. Money laundering involves concealing the origins of illegally obtained money by passing it through complex transactions or legitimate businesses to make it appear legal. Many countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws that criminalize such activities and impose significant penalties including fines and imprisonment.",
